nde2.methodcalls.delivery

Class GetTablesMethodCall

  • java.lang.Object
    • nde2.methodcalls.BaseMethodCall
      • nde2.methodcalls.delivery.BaseMethodCall
        • nde2.methodcalls.delivery.GetTablesMethodCall
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GetChildAreaTablesMethodCall

    public class GetTablesMethodCall
extends BaseMethodCall
    This method call wraps the NDE2 getTables REST call.

    This operation is a simplified version of getDataCube which it encapsulates. As well as making it easier for client applications to construct the request, this simplification is an essential precursor to offering a RESTful version of the service.

    A list of one or more Areas must be supplied.

    All other parameters are optional, but a NullPointerException will be thrown unless one or both of datasets and variables are supplied. If datasets but not variables are supplied, it is assumed that all the variables are wanted for these datasets.

    If no time period is given, then the latest data is returned, you get only the variables still in use by the latest version of the dataset, and no discontinued ones.

    Author:
    filip

      • getTables

        public List<Dataset> getTables()
                        throws XPathExpressionException,
                               ParserConfigurationException,
                               SAXException,
                               IOException,
                               NDE2Exception,
                               NullPointerException,
                               ParseException
        Calls the NDE2 Delivery service, requesting tables for the areas, dataset families or variable families specified in this GetTablesMethodCall.

        Note: This method is fairly long, and it connects to a remote host. It may take a while. There is nothing I can do to make it less painful. You should use it asynchronously.

        Returns:
        A list of tables, represented by Datasets, that contain the requested data.
        Throws:
        XPathExpressionException
        ParserConfigurationException
        SAXException
        IOException
        NDE2Exception - Thrown if the server returns an error-type response
        NullPointerException - Thrown if there are no DataSetFamilies or VariableFamilies specified. You should include at least one DataSetFamiliy.
        ParseException
